y, knowledge has been controlled by a powerful few. Wikipedia needs knowledge from all languages and cultures. The internet has become the default for accessing information—women, people of color, and the global south remain underrepresented. We invite you to help correct history.  Join the movement  Help us unlock the world’s knowledge.As a nonprofit, Wikipedia and our related free knowledge projects are powered primarily through donations.Donate now    Connect 											— 						 							اتصل						   					Stay up-to-date on our work.				     Get email updates Subscribe to news about ongoing projects and initiatives SubscribeThis mailing list is powered by MailChimp. The Wikimedia Foundation will handle your personal information in accordance with this site’s privacy policy.    Contact a humanQuestions about the Wikimedia Foundation or our projects? Get in touch with our team.ContactFollow  Facebook Twitter Instagram LinkedIn         Photo credits        			Wikimedia 2022 4020		 Wikimedia Foundation   		CC BY-SA 4.0	          			Wikimedia Sound Logo press release image-05		 Wikimedia Foundation   		CC BY-SA 4.0	           		Emily Temple-Wood at Wikimania 2014	  Victor Grigas/Wikimedia Foundation   		CC BY-SA 3.0	           		Armine Aghayan	  Victor Grigas   		CC BY-SA 3.0	           		Pranayraj Vangari	  Pranayraj Vangari   		CC BY-SA 4.0	          			foundation-web-banner-1		          		Wikimedia Conference 2017	  Jason Krüger/Wikimedia Deutschland e.V.   		CC BY-SA 4.0	           		Papaul_Tshibamba-3	  Victor Grigas   		CC BY SA 3.0	           		SOPA protest in Midtown NYC	  Zachary McCune   		CC BY-SA 4.0	           		Art+Feminism Wikipedia edit-a-thon	  Jens Mohr   		CC BY-SA 3.0	           The Wikimedia Foundation, Inc is a nonprofit charitable organization dedicated to encouraging the growth, development and distribution of free, multilingual content, and to providing the full content of these wiki-based projects to the public free of charge.  Careers Contact 